Hours Mon - Fri 8:00am - 5:00pm Sat - Sun Closed Book an Appointment: Rotator Cuff The rotator cuff is an intricate group of four small tendons that regulate movement of the The four tendons are: Supraspinatus Infraspinatus Subscapularis Teres The purpose of these four tendons are to maintain the position of the humeral head (ball) on the glenoid (socket) of the shoulder during These deep tendons around the shoulder are referred to as postural A postural muscle is one which is active with many fine and mundane movements in normal In contrast, the deltoid muscle provides power and strength to the shoulder and is primarily active with more strenuous There are two types of rotator cuff tears: Degenerative and While the rotator cuff does not directly contribute to power movements of the shoulder, significant damage to the rotator cuff leads to an “uncoupling” of the powerful deltoid from the shoulder Since the rotator cuff is involved in so many aspects of shoulder and arm use, it is vulnerable to wear and tear as we age, even from routine everyday The simplest issue involving the rotator cuff is shoulder bursitis, which involves inflammation of the bursa that lies on top of the rotator The purpose of the bursa is to cushion, lubricate and provide nutrition to the rotator cuff Since the bursa is very rich in nerve endings, inflammation of the bursa can be quite The same activities that can irritate the rotator cuff can also irritate the bursa, which tends to be a little more prone to irritation than the rotator cuff tendon Often, however, if not appropriately addressed, shoulder bursitis can be a precursor to development of rotator cuff tendonitis or even degenerative Fortunately, bursitis can be treated with nonsurgical Rotator cuff tendonitis is inflammation of the tendon itself, often following a prolonged course of This can be a more tenacious problem than bursitis but still typically does not require surgery for successful Rest, physical therapy and medications (either oral or injected) are typically successfully employed to treat these While surgery is occasionally necessary, this is not the norm in our office as our nonsurgical options have a high rate of Degenerative tears occur over one’s Two people with similar activities, compared side to side over time, may develop tears in their tendon at vastly different periods in their These differences are largely due to health and Certainly, prolonged strenuous use of the shoulder can make these tears more Additionally, bone spurs in the shoulder can mechanically damage the tendon over However, this phenomenon, known as external impingement, is less common than previously Degenerative tears occur over time and may not always be symptomatic Frequently these types of tears can be successfully treated with rest, physical therapy and injections, or a combination of these Surgical repair is a reasonable option for degenerative tears that don’t respond to nonsurgical Surgery is typically done in an outpatient setting and done Often, other minor issues which typically may not otherwise require surgery, such as arthritis, bone spurs and bursitis, are addressed at the same time as the rotator Conversely, traumatic tears occur suddenly, with Violent pulling of the arm, falling onto the shoulder and other types of trauma can cause the rotator cuff to acutely Top Free Automation Tools for Testing Desktop Applications By Joe Colantonio Blog Podcasts Conferences About Search return Back Blog Top Free Automation Tools for Testing Desktop Applications Automation Testing Published on: 09 2020 As a testing community we have been spoiled with a bunch of open source automation testing tools for browser and API automation testing , but what about tools for desktop application automation? I am often asked the question, “Do you know of an automation tool that can be used in automating applications?” If that’s you, here are the top free automation testing tools for desktop applications : WinAppDriver Windows Application Driver developed by Yousef Durr of Microsoft , it is the Windows implementation of Appium to automate Windows Windows Application Driver is a service to support UI Test Automation on Windows This service supports testing Universal Windows Platform (UWP), Windows Presentation Foundation (WPF), Windows Forms (WinForms) and Classic Windows (Win32) apps on Windows The Windows Application Driver complies with the JSON Wire Protocol standard and some application management functionalities defined by Appium . Winium Winium is a Selenium Remote WebDriver implementation for the automated testing of Windows applications based on WinFroms and WPF the Why Winium? section of their website, it mentions that You have Selenium WebDriver for testing web apps, and Appium for testing iOS and Android And now you have tools for testing Windows apps as What are some of the benefits? As said by Appium: You can write tests with your favorite dev tools using any language, including: Java, JavaScript with (in promise, callback or generator flavors), PHP, Python Ruby C# Clojure or Perl with the Selenium WebDriver API and client You can use any testing Sounds like a good reason to If it sounds good to you as well, you can check it out on their GitHub site where it currently has White Framework Do you need to automate a thick client application like WPF, Silverlight, Win32 or WinForms? If so, then the White framework may be the automation framework for White is an library from Test Like CodedUI, it has a more narrow scope it only targets desktop applications, not Web Both CodedUI and White are based on UI Automation Library for There aren’t many automation testing tools that handle software testing applications, so this is a valuable tool for folks who need to test such It’s also easy to get started using White . Jubula Need to test desktop Java applications? Jubula is an open source tool for automating UI tests designed specifically for Java It s also reasonably well known in the Eclipse It provides automated functional GUI testing for various types of It is aimed at teams who want their automated tests to be written by test experts from the user perspective, without requiring any coding Jubula tests incorporate best practices from software development to ensure maintainability of the automated I recently interviewed the product owner of Jubula, Alex Schladebeck , on Episode of Pywinauto Do you love using Python as your language for everything, and also need to automate Windows desktop applications? If so, check out It describes itself as a GUI automation library written in pure Python and well developed for Windows At its simplest, it allows you to send mouse and keyboard actions to dialogs and controls on both Windows and Linux, while more complex actions are supported on Windows only thus far (Linux support is under development). The latest release introduced MS UI Automation (UIA) support, which includes WinForms, WPF, Qt browsers, Store tests and Oracle Application Testing Suite Does your team do a lot of software development? Oracle Application Testing Suite (OATS) contains a bunch of integrated products to help with Oracle Functional Testing for regression testing of Web applications, and Oracle Load Testing for performance testing of your Oracle packaged Oracle explains that its Application Testing Suite is a comprehensive, integrated testing solution that ensures the quality, scalability, and availability of your Web applications, Web Services, packaged Oracle Applications, and Oracle This integrated, full lifecycle solution enables you to define and manage your application testing process, validate application functionality, and ensure that your applications will perform under With Application Testing Suite, you can deploy your Web applications and Web Services in less time while maximizing the efficiency of your testing Oracle Application Testing suite contains a bunch of integrated products to help with Oracle Functional Testing for regression testing of web applications and Oracle Load Testing for performance testing of your Oracle packaged So if you need a tool to help test your regression and performance test your Oracle applications or databases OATS is a must try SikuliX SikuliX can help automate anything you see on the screen of your desktop computer running Windows,

​ We all have passions, skills, likes, and dislikes that make us who we For many of us, it can be difficult to accept being different and However, it is so important to be your authentic self and embrace the parts of yourself that make you stand out from the ​ Growing up, I was constantly told to try to fit in and not stand out too much from the I felt like I had to wear a mask to appear It was only when I took off this mask that I started to realize that being different wasn t so bad after ​ I m a wife, a mother of seven children (including one on the autism spectrum), an entrepreneur, a marketing enthusiast, a hippie witch doctor, an introverted extrovert, hyperactive squirrel lady who wears resourcefulness as my badge of honor – just like many of you! ​ My past story has seen its fair share of bad and unfortunate parts but also some amazing perfect parts as It wasn t until recently that I decided to embrace all those aspects of myself that made me unique and stop comparing myself to Taking this step towards has been incredibly liberating for me more people should take this path! ​ Every day we are presented with opportunities to open ourselves up and accept our true selves without fear or Whether it s accepting your own uniqueness or celebrating others differences - these moments are integral in creating a better world for everyone around There is no doubt that embracing your authentic self takes time and patience but it is worth it in the long run because at the end of the day nobody can shine brighter than you if you just let yourself be YOU! So don t be afraid to show off all those qualities that make you special - there is nothing more powerful than being yourself! ​ So here s me waving hello! Hi there!
